TRIP COMMENTS: Santa Barbara Audubon Society trip led by Joan and George Hardie. Also present were Jim Hodgson, Melissa Kelly, Ron Hirst, Suzanne Barrymore, Carol Barrymore, and others. Overcast most of morning with temp. ranging from about 55F to 65F and B1 winds. The water was low, with very little open water at the east end of the Lake, although the rains of several days previously had opened a small channel and a small amount of water was flowing into the lake. Extensive mudflats were at the east end and as far west as the mouth of Horse Canyon. Some mudflats were on the main shore south of Arrowhead Island, but these hosted no shorebirds.

I arrived at about 9am on the south side of the lagoon, at the north end of Rios Ave. in Solana Beach. A Pacific Golden Plover had been reported the previous day, so I hoped to find this. I birded along the path to the east, where the bird had been reported the previous day, and I met up with Guy McCaskie and a small group of birders who had already located the plover. Afterwards, I birded the northwest corner of the lagoon, on the west side of the railroad tracks, and returned to Rios Ave. to bird along the trail to the west. Besides the plover, an adult in transition from alternate to basic plumage, the visit was notable for the huge number of terns present, mostly Elegants.

5th annual Big Sit :  George Chaniot, Chuck Vaughn, Vishnu, Barbara Dolan,  Matthew Matthiessen, Cheryl Watson ;  49-80 F ;  Lake level 7.33 feet. This is the highest lake level yet, and,probably not coincidentally, the lowest species count to date.  Today we set a new record low.  The weather was beautiiful again ;  clear and brilliant sky at 5:20, moon just past full,  Saturn with rings, Jupiter's moons, Orion nebula, shooting stars ;  high cirrus invaded from NW before dawn, slight breeze.  The remainder of the day had ~25% variable cirrus.  Beautiful day.
